{"type":"message","id":"e973e0fb","parentId":"ab34876c","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:12:44.955Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_wsscrn0watub_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 151214\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: experiment (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and decide on one concrete action.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals and pending work:\r\n- Phase 0 COMPLETE\r\n- Phase 1 COMPLETE (Architecture cross-analysis)\r\n- CFI Compression Experiment COMPLETE with key findings\r\n- Pending: Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\r\n\r\nThe key insight from this session is:\r\n- Formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n- This should distinguish \"constant format\" (freq≈160, CFI=1) from \"research trajectory\" (freq<120, CFI>0.5)\r\n\r\nThe next logical action is to run the Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment. I need to:\r\n1. Analyze the existing pulse data to calculate the hybrid scores\r\n2. Compare against binary thresholds\r\n3. Document results\r\n\r\nLet me look at what's available. The research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md has the data. I should:\r\n1. Read the current CFI compression synthesis to understand the data structure\r\n2. Design the hybrid scoring experiment\r\n3. Potentially run the analysis\r\n\r\nActually, I should create a new analysis document that:\r\n- Takes the existing CFI/freq data\r\n- Applies the hybrid formula\r\n- Compares precision/recall\r\n\r\nLet me check what files exist. I see pulse_2026-03-24 151114.md mentioned. The CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md should have the data I need.\r\n\r\nMy concrete action: Create the hybrid CFI×Freq scoring analysis, applying the new formula to the existing pulse data and comparing results against the binary thresholds.\r\n\r\nLet me write the mutation to create a new document: research/HYBRID_CFI_FREQ_EXPERIMENT.md\r\n\r\nThis will:\r\n1. Document the hybrid scoring formula\r\n2. Apply it to the existing 200 pulses of data\r\n\r\n\r\n3. Compare precision/recall against binary thresholds\r\n4. Determine if the formula successfully differentiates between constant format and research trajectory tokens\r\n\r\nI'll complete the final step of the experimental analysis, generating a comprehensive comparison that validates the new hybrid scoring approach.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI Compression experiment established that binary thresholds (CFI ≥ 0.7 AND freq < 60) are too aggressive, losing 92.9% recall. The key insight is that the hybrid formula score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120) should distinguish constant-format tokens (freq≈160, CFI=1, score=1.0) from research trajectory (freq<120, CFI>0.5, score varies).\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate hybrid scoring experiment document that applies the new formula to existing pulse data, compares precision/recall against binary thresholds, and determines if this approach resolves the constant-format contamination problem.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Hybrid CFI×Freq Scoring Experiment\r\n**Date:** 2026-03-24\r\n**Status:** IN PROGRESS\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nThe formula `score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)` will:\r\n1. Score constant-format tokens (freq=160, CFI=1.0) at 1.0 (unchanged)\r\n2. Score research tokens (freq<120, CFI>0.5) at proportional scores\r\n3. Allow threshold at score ≥ 0.3 to recover recall lost by pure CFI filtering\r\n\r\n## Expected Outcomes\r\n| Token Type | freq | CFI | Hybrid Score | Interpretation |\r\n|------------|------|-----|--------------|----------------|\r\n| \"for next instantiation\" | 160 | 1.00 | 1.00 | Constant format - will still be flagged |\r\n| \"pulse\" | 160 | 1.00 | 1.00 | Constant format - will still be flagged |\r\n| \"Phase 1\" | 136 | 0.96 | 0.96 | Research trajectory - OK |\r\n| \"architecture\" | 45 | 0.72 | 0.27 | Research trajectory - borderline |\r\n| \"compression\" | 12 | 0.58 | 0.058 | Rare but causal - SHOULD pass |\r\n\r\n## Analysis Plan\r\n1. Extract CFI and freq values from existing 200-pulse dataset\r\n2. Calculate hybrid scores for all tokens\r\n3. Compare threshold at score ≥ 0.3 vs binary CFI ≥ 0.7 AND freq < 60\r\n4. Measure precision/recall against manual relevance judgments\r\n\r\n## Next Step\r\nApply formula to pulse_2026-03-24 151114.md and existing CFI data.\r\nfile: research/HYBRID_CFI_FREQ_EXPERIMENT.md\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 15:12:35\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774379564954}}
